              "Documents to be filed in an application\n(2) A person wishing to apply for an estate grant must, after delivering in accordance with\nRule 25-2 the documents that were required to be delivered under that rule, file the\nfollowing documents:\n(a) a submission for estate grant in Form P2;\n(b) an affidavit from the applicant, or, if there are 2 or more applicants, from at\nleast one of the applicants, as follows:\n(i) if the application is for a grant of  <em>probate</em> or a grant of administration\nwith will annexed,\n(A) in Form P3 if subrule (6) of this rule applies, or\n(B) in Form P4 if subrule (6) of this rule does not apply;\n(ii) if the application is for a grant of administration without will\nannexed, in Form P5;\n(iii) if the application is for an anc illary grant of proba te or an ancillary\ngrant of administration with will annexed, in Form P6;\n(iv) if the application is for an an cillary grant of administration without\nwill annexed, in Form P7;\nConsolidation current to September 14, 2023"
